extent of
disagreement inside the U.S.
State Department

06:45.605 --> 06:47.974 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
about the course set by
President Obama.

06:48.074 --> 06:51.344 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Chief foreign affairs
correspondent Margaret
Warner reports.

06:51.444 --> 06:58.451 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: For five years,
the savage
Syria conflict has killed some
400,000 and

06:58.551 --> 07:00.620 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
put millions more to flight.

07:00.720 --> 07:06.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now 51 mid-level diplomatic
officials have
gone on record advocating a
dramatic shift

07:06.926 --> 07:12.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in U.S. strategy. They have
signed an internal
so-called dissent letter,
calling for targeted

07:12.766 --> 07:16.903 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
military strikes against
President Bashar
al-Assad's government.

07:17.003 --> 07:21.975 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The dissenters argue it would
help bring Assad
to the negotiating table and
deal a major

07:22.075 --> 07:27.447 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
blow to ISIS. The document
remains secret,
but Andrew Tabler, an expert on
Syria at the

07:27.547 --> 07:31.918 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Washington Institute for Near
East Policy,
is familiar with the document's
contents.

07:32.018 --> 07:35.221 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ANDREW TABLER, Fellow,
Washington Institute
for Near East Policy: If the
Assad regime

07:35.322 --> 07:41.628 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
violates the cessation of
hostilities and
uses it to further its position
on the battlefield,

07:41.728 --> 07:46.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in such cases, military force
could be used.
Second, if humanitarian
assistance is not

07:46.900 --> 07:50.670 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
provided or is impeded in some
way, military
force could be used.

07:50.770 --> 07:55.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: In Copenhagen
today, Secretary
of State John Kerry said he had
not yet seen

07:55.241 --> 07:56.976 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the memo, but welcomed it.

07:57.077 --> 07:59.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KERRY, U.S. Secretary of
State: I think
it's an important statement, and
I respect

07:59.746 --> 08:03.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the process very, very much, and
I will probably
meet with people or have a
chance to talk

08:03.550 --> 08:05.352 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with them when we get back.

08:05.452 --> 08:08.855 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: The memo came
through a channel
created for State Department
employees to

08:08.955 --> 08:17.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
register policy disagreements
without retaliation.
When conflict first broke out in
2011, President

08:17.530 --> 08:22.702 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Obama called for ousting Assad.
And in 2012,
he threatened military action.

08:22.802 --> 08:27.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
A red line for us is, we start
seeing a whole

08:27.273 --> 08:31.811 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
bunch of chemical weapons moving
around or
being utilized. That would
change my calculus.

08:31.911 --> 08:37.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: But after a
regime chemical
attack killed more than 1,000
Syrians in August

08:37.183 --> 08:43.456 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
2013, the president didn't
launch military
strikes, nor step up arming the
Syrian rebels.

08:43.556 --> 08:49.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
More recently, he's launched
U.S. airstrikes
in Syria, but only against ISIS.
Instead,

08:49.963 --> 08:54.868 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russia intervened last fall on
Assad's behalf,
bolstering him. Today, Russian
air attacks

08:54.968 --> 08:59.372 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hit anti-Assad rebels battling
is in Southern
Syria.

08:59.472 --> 09:04.711 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
A spokesman for Russian
President Vladimir
Putin warned today any U.S. move
targeting

09:04.811 --> 09:09.015 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Assad's forces would plunge the
region into
total chaos.

09:09.115 --> 09:10.950 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Andrew Tabler's response?

09:11.051 --> 09:13.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANDREW TABLER: If you look at
this, over time,
whether it's the United States
and the threat

09:13.987 --> 09:20.693 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of use of military force in 2013
or Israel's
continued use of strikes inside
of Syria,

09:20.794 --> 09:23.329 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this is something that the Assad
regime is
known to respond to.

09:23.430 --> 09:28.435 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: All of this
comes as a February
cease-fire has largely
dissolved. It did let

09:28.535 --> 09:34.741 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
humanitarian aid reach some
Syrian communities,
but others remain cut off by
Assad loyalists.

09:34.841 --> 09:39.546 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And peace talks backed by
Secretary of State
Kerry and the Russians have
shown no progress.

09:39.646 --> 09:46.186 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
